Cardi B photo WMagazine At the MTV Video Music Awards set to take place on Monday, Cardi B would be performing for the first time since becoming a mother at the New York’s Radio City Music Hall. Along with Cardi, Nicki Minaj, Travis Scott, Post Malone, Logic, Ariana Grande, Shawn Mendes and this year’s Michael Jackson Vanguard recipient Jennifer Lopez will also grace the stage. Cardi would be opening this years MTV Video Music Awards and with 10 nominations, it could be a busy night for Cardi B. She has been nominated as the artist of the year, best new artist, and best hip-hop video for Bartier Cardi – a duet with 21 Savage. The singer shared this on her Instagram; See you there ! A post shared by  CARDIVENOM (@iamcardib) on Aug 15, 2018 at 1:28pm PDT 